    {"question_text": "What is the correct implementation for an agent that manages its own energy/compute budget across a long session?", "option_a": "Use maximum compute for every action", "option_b": "Track cumulative token usage and latency, estimate remaining budget based on session limits, allocate more compute to high-value decisions (complex reasoning, important outputs) and less to routine ones (simple lookups, formatting), implement a 'low power mode' for when budget is nearly exhausted (shorter responses, fewer tool calls, more caching), and warn users when quality may degrade", "option_c": "Stop processing when budget hits 50% used", "option_d": "Use minimum compute for all actions to conserve budget", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "agent_architecture"},
    {"question_text": "In an agent architecture, what is the correct approach for implementing incremental task completion with partial delivery?", "option_a": "Only deliver results when 100% complete", "option_b": "Identify natural delivery milestones within a complex task, produce usable partial results at each milestone (e.g., deliver sections of a document as they're written), clearly communicate what's done vs pending, allow user feedback on partial results to influence remaining work, and support task reprioritization based on which partial deliveries are most valuable", "option_c": "Deliver everything at once regardless of size", "option_d": "Deliver a percentage of the result at fixed time intervals", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "agent_architecture"},
    {"question_text": "When implementing an agent that needs to maintain consistency across multiple related outputs, what is the correct approach?", "option_a": "Generate each output independently without cross-referencing", "option_b": "Maintain a consistency ledger: track facts, decisions, and terminology established in earlier outputs, provide this ledger as context when generating later outputs, implement post-generation consistency checking that compares new output against established facts, flag and resolve any contradictions before delivery, and version the ledger as outputs are accepted", "option_c": "Regenerate all outputs every time any one changes", "option_d": "Only ensure consistency within a single output, not across outputs", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "agent_architecture"},
    {"question_text": "What is the correct pattern for implementing an agent that uses active learning to minimize the information it needs from users?", "option_a": "Ask all possible questions upfront before starting any work", "option_b": "Identify the minimum information needed to proceed, ask targeted questions that maximize information gain (questions whose answers most reduce uncertainty about the task), use default assumptions for non-critical details, validate assumptions in context rather than asking explicitly, and learn which questions are typically unnecessary for specific task types", "option_c": "Never ask questions; always guess based on available context", "option_d": "Ask one question per interaction turn regardless of relevance", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "agent_architecture"},
