    {"question_text": "In a multi-agent system, what is the correct approach for implementing knowledge transfer between agents?", "option_a": "Each agent learns independently without sharing", "option_b": "Formalize discovered knowledge into shareable formats (templates, rules, examples), implement a knowledge marketplace where agents can publish and subscribe to relevant knowledge, validate transferred knowledge before integration (what works for one agent may not work for another), track knowledge provenance, and measure the impact of transferred knowledge on receiving agent performance", "option_c": "Clone the entire memory of one agent to another", "option_d": "Only share raw data without any processing or context", "correct_answer": "B", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "agent_architecture"},
