    {"question_text": "When implementing an agent that needs to coordinate multiple tools in a specific sequence, what orchestration pattern ensures reliability?", "option_a": "Use a simple fixed approach without adaptation", "option_b": "Only handle the most common scenario without edge cases", "option_c": "Define tool execution sequences as declarative workflows with explicit dependencies, validate preconditions before each tool invocation, handle tool failures with step-specific retry and fallback strategies, support partial execution recovery without re-running successful steps, and maintain execution traces for debugging and optimization", "option_d": "Defer all complex scenarios to human operators", "correct_answer": "C", "difficulty": "advanced", "topic": "agent_architecture"},
